    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Cambridge</placeName>
                    <date>11 March 1858</date>
                    <salute>My dear Professor</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I find that M. <hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Bentham’s statement about the money allowed by the Senate for arranging the Lehmann collection &amp; the payments already made to him is quite correct. If you think it right that he should be paid the whole remaining 50£, alltho’ his work is not just finished, &amp; will give me such opinion in writing for the satisfaction of my auditors, I will pay the money to him, or I will pay him another instalment of 25£ or 30£, just as you think proper.</p>
                  <p>I am sorry that I was engaged when you did me the favor to call this morning</p>
                  <p>Yours truly | H. Philpott V.C</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
